{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.30",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 30,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 30 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:1",
      "text": "He who loves his son will continue to lay stripes upon him, that he may have joy from him in the end.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:2",
      "text": "He who chastises his son will have profit from him, and will brag about him among his acquaintances.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:3",
      "text": "He who teaches his son will provoke his enemy to jealousy. Before friends, he will rejoice in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:4",
      "text": "His father dies, and is as though he had not died; for he has left one behind him like himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:5",
      "text": "In his life, he saw his son and rejoiced. When he died, it was without regret.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:6",
      "text": "He left behind him an avenger against his enemies, and one to repay kindness to his friends.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:7",
      "text": "He who makes too much of his son will bind up his wounds. His heart will be troubled at every cry.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:8",
      "text": "An unbroken horse becomes stubborn. An unrestrained son becomes headstrong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:9",
      "text": "Pamper your child, and he will make you afraid. Play with him, and he will grieve you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:10",
      "text": "Don’t laugh with him, lest you have sorrow with him, and you gnash your teeth in the end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:11",
      "text": "Give him no liberty in his youth, and don’t ignore his follies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:12",
      "text": "Bow down his neck in his youth, and beat him on the sides while he is a child, lest he become stubborn, and be disobedient to you, and there be sorrow to your soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:13",
      "text": "Chastise your son, and give him work, lest his shameless behavior be an offense to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:14",
      "text": "Better is a poor man who is healthy and fit, than a rich man who is afflicted in his body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:15",
      "text": "Health and fitness are better than all gold, and a strong body better than wealth without measure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:16",
      "text": "There is no wealth better than health of body. There is no gladness above the joy of the heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:17",
      "text": "Death is better than a bitter life, and eternal rest than a continual sickness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:18",
      "text": "Good things poured out upon a mouth that is closed are like food offerings laid upon a grave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:19",
      "text": "What does an offering profit an idol? For it can’t eat or smell. So is he who is punished by the Lord,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:20",
      "text": "seeing with his eyes and groaning, like a eunuch embracing a virgin and groaning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:21",
      "text": "Don’t give your soul to sorrow. Don’t afflict yourself deliberately.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:22",
      "text": "Gladness of heart is the life of a man. Cheerfulness of a man lengthens his days.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:23",
      "text": "Love your own soul, and comfort your heart. Remove sorrow far from you, for sorrow has destroyed many, and there is no profit in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:24",
      "text": "Envy and wrath shorten life. Anxiety brings old age before its time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.30.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 30:25",
      "text": "Those who are cheerful and merry will benefit from their food.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
